spec: as3346
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 670 (as3346): __neg__, __pos__, __abs__ dict-presence (unary -x, +x, abs(x)) for asyncio types."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.PriorityQueue, asyncio.LifoQueue."
    - "Key finding (__neg__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __neg__. Unary negation (__neg__, -x) belongs to the numeric data model. asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives — none of them model a numeric magnitude that could be negated. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition are boolean-state synchronization guards; -event is not a defined Python expression. asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore manage a permit counter fully encapsulated behind acquire()/release() coroutines; the integer counter is not exposed for unary negation. asyncio.Task/Future are pending coroutine result handles; -task is undefined. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue are ordered item stores with no numeric data model at all."
    - "Key finding (__pos__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __pos__. Unary plus (__pos__, +x) is the mirror of __neg__ and equally belongs to the numeric data model. asyncio types define no numeric protocol of any kind — confirmed across waves 658–669 (all arithmetic, reflected arithmetic, and in-place arithmetic operators are false for all 10 types). +event, +task, +queue are not valid Python expressions for asyncio objects. asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: the permit counter is internal and not exposed for +semaphore. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores with no numeric unary operator semantics."
    - "Key finding (__abs__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __abs__. The abs() built-in delegates to __abs__, which is part of the numeric data model (numbers.Number). asyncio types implement no numeric magnitude. abs(event), abs(task), abs(queue) are not meaningful operations for synchronization primitives, coroutine handles, or item stores. Wave 658 established that __add__ is false for all 10 asyncio types — the complete absence of arithmetic operations (waves 658–669) makes __abs__ equally absent."
    - "Continues the all-false run from wave 656 (__call__/__len__/__getitem__) through wave 670 (__neg__/__pos__/__abs__) — fifteen consecutive waves of 100% false results for asyncio types."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 660 (as3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 661 (as3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 662 (as3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 664 (as3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 665 (as3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 666 (as3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 667 (as3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 668 (as3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 669 (as3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 670 (as3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 10."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __neg__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__neg__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __neg__.
# Unary negation (__neg__, -x) is a numeric data model method. asyncio types
#   are coroutine-based concurrency primitives with no numeric magnitude.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization guards;
#   -event is not a defined Python expression.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-counter objects whose internal
#   integer state is fully encapsulated behind acquire()/release() coroutines.
#   The counter is not exposed for unary negation.
# asyncio.Task/Future: pending coroutine result handles; -task and -future
#   are not valid Python expressions.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: ordered item stores with no numeric
#   data model; -queue is not a defined Python expression.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

