# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __abs__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__abs__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __abs__.
# The abs() built-in delegates to __abs__, part of the numeric data model
#   (numbers.Number). asyncio types implement no numeric magnitude.
# abs(event), abs(task), abs(queue) are not meaningful operations for
#   synchronization primitives, coroutine handles, or item stores.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state guards; magnitude is not a
#   concept for lock or event objects.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: the permit counter is internal and not
#   exposed through any numeric data model method, including __abs__.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; abs() is not applicable to
#   pending result objects. Results are obtained via await or result().
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores; abs(queue) is not
#   defined. Queue length is obtained via qsize(), not abs().
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

